commit.message: Print Lua version when running tests.
Add support for Lua 5.4
Update install docs a little.
Provide the Lua implementation name/version via "LuaRuntime.lua_implementation".
Provide the Lua runtime version via "lupa.LUA_VERSION" and "LuaRuntime.lua_version".
Make "IS_PY2" a compile time constant.
Fix Mandelbrot code example and use Pillow instead of PIL in it.
Prepare release of lupa 1.9.
Update bundled Lua to 5.3.5.

Include "lua53" etc. in package search and CI builds.
Make sure there is only one Lua version installed in travis CI and thus the expected one is used.
Closes #126.
Use "os.RTLD_*" flags in Py3, as "DLFCN.*" is only the right thing to use in Py2.
Update Python versions in CI build config.
Add "make sdist" target.
Upgrade minimum Cython version to 0.29.3.
Prepare release of 1.8.
Minor safety fix for typed assignment.
Modernise Cython language level to 3str.
Automatically rebuild with Cython from Makefile if available.

Fix ABC import in Py3.
Closes GH-107.
Prepare release of Lupa 1.7.
Include logo in sdist.
Prepare release of Lupa 1.7.
Fix a potential crash on Python shutdown when trying to create a traceback entry for an exception, by statically disabling C-lines in tracebacks.
Add logo.
Provide appveyor feedback on most relevant py-versions first.
Revert test script in appveyor back to setup.py run.
Depend on stdint.h in MSVC used by Py3.4+, which should have it.
Avoid dependency on stdint.h on Windows, which MSVC lacks in Py2.7 etc.
Remove need for external "lupa_defs.h" file.
